  "handbook-introduction-title": "Medieval Architecture Mod",
  "handbook-introduction-text": "Medieval Architecture<br><br><i>This mod is a test to gather insights for my mod Age of Confession. Except for a few shapefiles, everything in this mod has been rebuild and the entire code has been rewritten. Thanks to the Attribute Rendering Library, I can now add significantly more blocks without compromising performance. <br>I would be very grateful for any feedback, as this will help me make Age of Confession usable for more people again.</i><br><br><strong>Archways</strong><br>To build the archways you have to build a construction frame first and place it in the world. Add loose stones, mortar and a block of your choice to finish the archway. The amount required depends on the size of the archway. For a 1-block archway, you need 6 loose stones, one batch of mortar and one block. For larger archways, multiply the amount by the area covered by the archway.",


